  "text": "In what follows, we will study the distribution of the residual speckle noise in the processed frame. The presence of a planet disturbs the tail distribution as planets are precisely detected as outliers in the processed frame. Hence the study of the tail decay requires planet-free datasets. An option is to remove all known planetary signals with, for instance, the negative companion injection method (NEGFC) [CITATION_1] . However, this method does not guarantee that the totality of the planetary signal is removed as it cannot be used for extended sources or faint planetary signals that are not previously detected.",
